<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">
                            <persName>Eisenhower</persName> Library, <persName corresp="#p_HJC1">Hagerty</persName> papers</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Excerpt From the Diary of <persName corresp="#p_HJC1" type="from">James C. Hagerty</persName>, Press Secretary to the
                                    <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-18">June 18, 1954</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In at 8:15.</p>
                        <p>
                            <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Allen Dulles</persName> called early in the
                            morning to tell me that his organization expected there would be an
                            anti-Communist uprising in Guatemala very shortly. Officially we don’t
                            know anything about it. The story broke late Friday night.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                    </div>
